# shadcn design language gate

Before implementing or changing any UI in scope of this rule, **stop and check shadcn’s design language** — do not invent one-off spacing, chrome, or interaction patterns.

## Required check (before coding)

1. Prefer existing `src/renderer/components/ui/*` primitives (`Button`, `Dialog`, `Input`, `Label`, `DropdownMenu`, etc.).
2. Align with shadcn / New York defaults when unsure:
   - Dialog: `p-6`, content `gap-4`; header title + description only; close control top-right
   - Stacks: form fields `gap-2` (label↔control), sections `gap-4`
   - Footer actions: `DialogFooter` / consistent button hierarchy
   - Interactive: `cursor-pointer` on clickable controls; disabled → `not-allowed`
3. If the request conflicts with shadcn patterns (custom chrome, ad-hoc padding reset, non-primitive menus), **call it out and confirm** before coding — do not silently diverge.
4. Map colors to existing token / CSS variables (`--ds-*`, shadcn semantic vars). Do not introduce a second palette.

## Do

```tsx
// ✅ Dialog content uses default padding/gap; fields in a gap-4 stack
<DialogContent className="sm:max-w-sm">
  <DialogHeader>
    <DialogTitle>…</DialogTitle>
    <DialogDescription>…</DialogDescription>
  </DialogHeader>
  <div className="flex flex-col gap-4">…</div>
  <DialogFooter>…</DialogFooter>
</DialogContent>
```

## Don’t

```tsx
// ❌ Zero out dialog spacing then hand-roll inconsistent padding
<DialogContent className="gap-0 p-0">
  <div className="p-3">…</div>
</DialogContent>
```

```css
/* ❌ Unlayered universal margin/padding reset that overrides Tailwind utilities */
* { margin: 0; padding: 0; }
```

## Out of scope

Shell layout tokens (`.application-shell`, `.titlebar-drag`, `.sidebar-rail`, tab bar chrome) and the xterm terminal island may stay project-specific. Interactive overlays, forms, menus, and buttons still follow shadcn.
